               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus letter from Egypt addressed to a prostates, a spiritual leader. Contains instructions about various matters relating to Apa Kire, Kyriakos and others. Farewell reads "May we prosper through your holy prayers." Verso has a voucher in Greek (P.Duk.inv. 435 V)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 13.3 x 31.4 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">13 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the recto; the address written along the fibers on the verso; written along the fibers on the verso in a different hand</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1.5 cm.; lower margin of 1-0.5 cm.; left margin of 1 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 435 R was formerly P.Miss. 1 R</note>
